```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 13, 12, 14, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'williamjallen', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928169286, 'comment_body': 'Can you add foreign keys for the user id and gradeable id', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 23, 22, 5, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928169323, 'comment_body': 'Would there be a case where we want g_id as null?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 23, 22, 5, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928169795, 'comment_body': 'Since these queries are quite similar, you could probably just concatenate strings to form this query to reduce the amount of duplicated code. There are a couple other queries in this file that do something like that.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 23, 22, 11, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928169961, 'comment_body': 'This ternary operator of if its a team do 2 separate things seems to be used quite often. Could we perhaps add a function in the Submitter class to get the respective team or anon id based on which it is to reduce these a bit?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 23, 22, 13, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928302782, 'comment_body': "Ideally you shouldn't have to do this but I know it won't work otherwise. I just made an issue https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/issues/8209 to track this. This is definitely correct for now but if that issue gets resolved before this goes in then I'd remove it.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 19, 31, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928306510, 'comment_body': 'Done', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 20, 9, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928306662, 'comment_body': 'Currently, there is no such place, so, default value has been removed.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 20, 10, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928306823, 'comment_body': 'String concatenation is used now.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 20, 11, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928307029, 'comment_body': 'A check inside `Submitter::getAnonId()` was already added, so all those ternary operators have been removed and replaced with a call similar to `$graded_gradeable->getSubmitter()->getAnonId($graded_gradeable->getGradeableId())`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 20, 13, 46, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928307405, 'comment_body': 'Okay :thumbsup:', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 20, 17, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 929110488, 'comment_body': 'Why commit and possibly do a rollback if you never start a transaction?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 25, 17, 4, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 929116095, 'comment_body': 'Why not pass $g_id into this function?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 25, 17, 11, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 929594924, 'comment_body': 'Oh, it was left there when I copied the template from one of the functions above. This has been removed.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 26, 7, 0, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 929597997, 'comment_body': "If `$g_id` isn't passed then all `anon_ids` in the table are returned. I intended to keep the `anon_ids` unique across gradeables, but thinking about it again I don't think it is necessary, it's just increasing the number of ids to loop over and thus increasing the computation time, so it has now been modified to send `$g_id` too.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 26, 7, 4, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 932443644, 'comment_body': "Should we also add a UNIQUE key here of g_id and anon_d? I know one of the scripts makes sure to not repeat an anon_id but I don't see how it could be harmful to make our database also guarantee it.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 28, 16, 21, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 932556364, 'comment_body': "I don't think `g_id` is unique, all the users in `gradeable_anon` have an entry for the same `g_id`. Also, after modifying User.php to send `$g_id` i.e. `$anon_ids = $this->core->getQueries()->getAllAnonIdsByGradeable($g_id)`, `anon_id` is not guaranteed to be unique when whole table is considered, it is only unique in the context of a particular gradeable, practically it can be expected to be unique across the table but not theoretically.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 28, 18, 33, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 932565348, 'comment_body': "I was referring that there can be a unique key/constraint consisting of BOTH g_id and anon_id. I know there can definitely be multiple g_id's and possibly multiple anon_id's but there should never be a multiple rows where the g_id and anon_id are both equal.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 28, 18, 45, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 932566314, 'comment_body': 'Here is an example of this https://github.com/Submitty/Submitty/blob/2590ba5ea747dda50b5e1f7e862de9f582292e72/migration/migrator/data/course_tables.sql#L1853', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 28, 18, 46, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cjreed121', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 932566668, 'comment_body': 'Oh, okay, my bad. Thanks for the help.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 28, 18, 47, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934777246, 'comment_body': 'Should we consider anon team id here', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 17, 53, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Eceptonsu', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 934903967, 'comment_body': 'Looking at some related code, it feels like it should be there. Surprising that no unexpected behavior was ever reported due to this on production machine.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 1, 20, 41, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'akshatbatra', 'type': 'User'}]
